&lt;p&gt;Clinical- Quality Improvement Officer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;30 hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based in Lincoln&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary Scale : £29,595 per annum, Pro rata &lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;_________________________________________________________&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St Barnabas Hospice has a vacancy for a Quality Improvement Officer to work as part of the Governance &amp; Education Team. This is an exciting opportunity to lead a programme of work to develop and improve services for the benefit of patients, staff and the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Quality Improvement Officer will work as an integral part of the Clinicial Governance team to co-ordinate and embed all aspects of good governance and continuous quality improvement across Trust clinical and non-clinical services. The post holder will facilitate and undertake an annual programme of audit and other quality improvement projects to ensure services continue to develop and are safe and compliant with regulatory and national standards for patients, their families and for our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will also include collation and analysis of data to support managers in measuring performance targets through audit, providing reports, including narrative, graphics and spread sheets. They will also be responsible for facilitation of patient and carer feedback ensuring that suggestions, concerns or complaints are recorded and that any actions identified are promptly implemented and evaluated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for the day to day management and championing of the Trust quality improvement agenda by engaging with and motivating colleagues to generate ideas to nurture a culture of quality improvement across Trust services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications and Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will require a &lt;strong&gt;clinical registered professional qualification&lt;/strong&gt; and have excellent organisational and communication skills with the knowledge of quality improvement and audit. They will be required to be competent with IT including Microsoft word, Excel and PowerPoint.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contract: &lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: &lt;strong&gt;30&lt;/strong&gt; hrs per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contributory pension scheme or continuation of NHS pension&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Buying and selling of annual leave and lease car schemes are options available to qualifying new employees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details please contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joy Fairweather, Governance and Education lead on 07864969750&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joy.fairweather@stbarnabashospiceco.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To apply for this position complete the online application process via NHS Jobs website. Please email hrteam@stbarnabashospice.co.uk if you are having problems completing the application form.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For assistance please contact -recruitment@stbarnabashospice.co.uk &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Please note we do not accept CV’s only completed application forms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St Barnabas Hospice is an Equal Opportunities Employer it believes in treating everyone with dignity and respect and encourages applications from all sectors of the community.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We reserve the right to extend, withdraw or close vacancies where necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that if you are selected for an interview you will be contacted via the email account you used to register on this site. Please check your spam folder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The closing date for completed applications is: 13.11.2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will be held on 27.11.2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
